name: JIRA

parameters.name: where
parameters.description: The CEQL search expression. Either id, updated or deleted is required. Note, the value for `updated` and `deleted` can be only `true`. To return results for specific ids, you should pass `id`, eg. id in (10200,10300). To return updated or deleted results after a certain date you can pass since, eg. updated='true'and since='121438013671562' . If since is not passed, it will default to 0. To return extra properties on an updated or id request, you can pass expand, eg.updated='true' and expand='issue.id,name'.
